The unfiltered, raw reaction of finding out the gender of our baby 🤭!! In honor of finding out the gender of our baby girl a week ago, I thought I’d be open about how I trult felt in that moment.  While I’m so excited to do all the cute, girly things with my baby and having a mini bestie… this was my initial reaction. And its not that I was disappointed or didnt want her. I was overfilled with so many emotions, and essentially so many fears/worries.  In my own life, I had just been through so much trauma and heart ache. The thought of having a girl, in an unplanned pregnancy, with what feels like no time to prepare, scared the heck out of me. I couldnt help but think I wasnt ready to raise a girl or not where I want to be yet to have essentially a little me… looking up to me. I just had such an overwhelming fear of my daughter experiencing the things I have gone through and wanting to protect her.  But I dont believe any of that, and in fact, I rebuke it. I am excited for this journey, and also do see how motherhood will be another journey of healing parts of me I didnt know still needed it.  Also, I am so grateful for my partner. It’s so important to know and choose the person you want to do life with. Im grateful to have a man that will sit with me, let me feel, comfort me, and encourage me. Off camera, he said, “I think youll be a much greater girl mom than you think”. I love that I get to do this with him 💕  #pregnancy #genderreveal #unfiltered #motherhoodjourney #couple #christian #relationships #faith #healingjourney

Lol PitMasterD😂 Caribbean Inspired Chicken Wings Ingredients 5 lbs chicken wings Marinade: 2 limes, juiced 1/4 cup orange juice 1/4 cup olive oil 1/4 cup dark soy sauce 2 tablespoon brown sugar 5 scallions, chopped 2 scotch bonnet peppers (or habaneros), chopped 1 yellow onion, chopped 6 cloves garlic 8-12 sprigs thyme (more is fine I love the flavor) 1 tablespoon salt 2 thick slices ginger 1 teaspoon allspice (+ add 8 berries) 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg *This recipe works on all chicken pieces. I like wings because it's more of a good time to eat and you know I like a gooood time😅 Instructions: Add all marinade ingredients in blender and pulse. You can pulse it and leave it chunky or blend till smooth. Pour 3/4 of the marinade over chicken and leave in fridge overnight. (FOR GRILLING) When it's time to grill get your grill to 300 degrees and cook over indirect heat with your favorite smoking chips (pecan or apple for me). 20 minutes in flip and apply reserved marinade. Cook for 20 more minutes. Then finish the wings cooking over the fire until desired char if you desire. I like my chicken touched by fire! & ( FOR BAKING IN THE OVEN) Add marinaded chicken in a pan, single layered. Bake at 350 for 20 minutes then rotate the wings. Increase to 425 and bake until brown and deep color appears, about 25-30 minutes. (Timing could be less or more based on your oven, how much you are cooking at a time, the pan, etc. so watch your food!) #cook #cooking #chef #grilling #dadlife #bbq @biggreenegg

There shouldn’t be a need to demand increased accessibility for education. Treating chronic illness and managing disability shouldn’t come at the cost of anyone’s education, career, or personal goals. BEEF PHO- STOVE TOP  This is a much more complicated pho recipe. I made a lot cause family was in town. If you want a simplified broth recipe, let me know =)  7.5 lbs beef bones 1.5 lbs beef brisket 2 lbs beef shank 4.5 lbs beef ribs 1.5 oz bag old man pho spice bag* 2 or 3 rock sugar, the size of a golf ball each 2 large onions 2 large ginger 1.5 TBSP sauce 10 quarts water ADDITIONAL SEASONING  1/2 cup fish sauce 2 TBSP chicken bouillon TOPPINGS: Onion, thinly sliced Cilantro, chopped Scallion, chopped Culantro Basil Bean sprouts Beef shank, thinly sliced Beef brisket, thinly sliced Beef ribs 1. We need to par-boil/ blanch our beef. In a large stock pot, fill it with beef bones, beef brisket, beef shank and beef ribs. Fill the pot with water and bring it over high heat. Bring to boil and let it cook for 5-10 mins. There will be scum that floats to the top. After 5-10 mins, turn off heat, rinse and drain beef under cold water. 2. While you ur beefs were blanching, prepare your aromatics. Peel your onion. Slice your ginger in half and char them.  (Note: You can do it on an open fire, air fryer or broiler. I had mine broiling for 10 mins each side)  3. oast ur spices on a dry skillet. This should not take long… 3-5 mins. Place your spice into the bag it comes with and set this aside.  4. In a clean large stock pot, fill it back with your blanched beef bones, beef brisket, beef shank and beef ribs along with your charred onions, charred ginger, rock sugar, salt and 10 quarts of water. Bring this to a boil. Once boiling. Reduce heat and cook for at least 7 hours. 5. After 2 or 3 hours, remove your beef shank, beef brisket and beef ribs. Place into an ice bath Fill your pot with water as needed. Allow you brisket and shank to cool before thinly slicing. (Note:I only fill it up with water1-2 times. I fill it up with water after taking out the beef shank, brisket and ribs. And the second time I fill back up with water is around the 5 or 6 hour mark of simmering.) 6. When there is 30-60 mins left of your simmering process, I like to add my spice bag. You may add your spice longer if you’d like. My parents don’t like pho with a strong spice so I limit to 30-60 mins.  7. After a total of 7 hours of simmering, remove everything in side— spice bag, onions, ginger, and beef bones.  8. Pour your broth thru a fine strainer. Allow broth to cool before placing into the fridge. The fat on top of your broth will harden, remove this. I actually left mine outside because it’s really cold rn and had the fat harden that way. Return broth back to stove and season to preference. I seasoned with 1/2 cup fish sauce and 2 TBSP chicken bouillon.  9. Assemble your bowl with your preferred toppings and ladle your broth over. Make sure your broth is boiling when you ladle it into your bowl. I have a video on how to do this posted before this one =)

Wash parsley, cilantro, and fenugreek. Pat dry and chop very finely. 2. Heat a dry pan on low heat and add olive oil and onions. Add meat to pan after onions caramelized.  3. Add turmeric, salt, and pepper.  4. Once meat has browned add herbs and  sauté the herbs for about 10 minutes until they dry out a bit.  5. Add 3 cups of water and bring to boil, then turn the heat to medium-low so it simmers lightly. The dish should be thick.  6. Largeelr #qipao/#cheongsam exist and can fit midsize and plus size bodies. Tips 👇 🇺🇲If you're in the Unites States like me... I like that East Meets Dress and @Beth and Brian Qipao  have plus-size sections on their sites! 📏Get a measuring tape and confirm which size will fit you best Since qipao are figuring hugging, the size may not fit perfectly, like it may be baggy in some areas.  🪡If you want it more figure hugging, you may need to get it tailored and taken in for parts of your body where it's loose. Alternatively, you can get one custom made, like from @Tanjerine Studios   - she makes gorgeous sequin qipao! 🇨🇳If you're in or visiting China... I bought the red qipao in this video this way! I used the app Taobao to search   🔑Use the term 大码 which means large size with he clothing you're searching for.  Find clothing that caters to our size. They usually will size 3XL and higher. 📏Get a measuring tape and confirm if the sizes listed online fits you Be prepared that you may find super cute qipao that doesn't fit you since Asian sizes run small 😥 I had a few moments of wanting to give up before I figured out using 大码 🩷Good luck! Shopping for Asian cultural clothing can be disappointing so don't feel like you're not enough. Asian sizes are known to run small!

But no matter what they will be juicy, crispy, and elevate your heart rate with excitement and triglycerides. At somewhere around 8-9 dollars per sandwich, this place is very affordable, honestly I’d even call it cheap these days, and the taste and quality is superb. Highly recommend Yas Chicken for their sandwiches and other random Asian-inspired bites. Let’s make some delicious Air Fryer Creamy Cajun Salmon Fries with @airfrypapi! 🤩 He used Grown In Idaho® #SuperCrispy Crinkle Cut Fries to quickly whip up the best thing you’ve never had — recipe below! #airfryerpapi  💥 Pro tip: If you’re using a multi-shelf air fryer, the fries, salmon and creamy Cajun sauce (cooked on the stove) can all be made in under 25 min! #growninidaho 🍟 Creamy Cajun Salmon Fries: 1 pkg Grown In Idaho® Super Crispy Crinkle Cut Fries 2 salmon fillets, skinless 1 tbsp olive oil 2 tbsp Cajun seasoning 1 tbsp lemon pepper seasoning 1 tbsp paprika 🐟 Creamy Cajun Sauce:  1/2 cup heavy cream 1/2 cup chicken stock 1/2 cup sun dried tomatoes, chopped 1 cup spinach 1 onion, medium and diced 1 tbsp garlic, minced 1 tbsp Cajun seasoning 1/3 cup Parmesan, grated 2 tbsp butter, unsalted Directions: 1. Preheat air fryer to 400 degrees. 2. In a shallow bowl, coat salmon fillets with olive oil. Sprinkle fillets evenly with Cajun seasoning and lemon pepper seasoning. 3. Air fry salmon fillets for 8-12 min or until internal temperature reaches 135 degrees at the thickest part. 4. Air fry Grown In Idaho® Super Crispy Crinkle Cut Fries according to package instructions. 5. In a pan on medium heat, add butter and onion. Cook until they become translucent. Add garlic and cook for 1 min. Add sun dried tomatoes and Cajun seasoning and cook for 1 min, then pour in the chicken stock and cream. Add Parmesan and stir in until it melts. Add spinach and immediately turn to medium-low heat. Simmer for 5-7 min. Sauce will thicken. 6. Build your plate! Start with a bed of fries, next add a salmon fillet, then top with a pour of creamy Cajun sauce. One of my favorite easy breakfasts  If you want to eat more protein in the morning but are tired of the same repetitive egg recipes, try these Chinese silken eggs.  They’re easy to prepare, melt in your mouth, and are the quickest savory breakfasts!   Recipe: - Beat 2 eggs in a bowl - Mix in 3/4 cup water and a pinch of salt (you can use chicken broth instead of water if you want more flavor) - Pour the egg mixture through a strainer and into a bowl.  Remove any air bubbles with a spoon. - Cover bowl with saran wrap and steam for 12 min - After 12 min, remove from steamer and top with 2 tsp soy sauce, 1 tsp sesame oil, and green onions. - Optional: Make cuts in steamed eggs to let the sauce seep through!  #easybreakfast #easymeal #asianfood #eggs #chinesesteamedeggs
